 Mandatory Palestine, directed by Leopold Jessner. While the focus of the book is on post-1990s productions across Europe and the USA, and on film, the Segue provides a broad survey of the interpretative shifts in the play’s performance from the 1930s to the second decade of the twenty-first century. Individual chapters explore productions by Peter Zadek, Trevor Nunn, Robert Sturua, Edward Hall, Rupert Goold, Daniel Sullivan, and Karin Coonrod. An extensive film section including silent film offers close analysis of Don Selwyn’s Te Tangata Whai Rawa o Weniti and Michael Radford’s adaptation. Accessible and engaging, the book will interest students, academics, and general readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAntisemitism in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Shakespeare.2bisacsh  aDon Selwyn.  aEdward Hall.  aLeopold Jessner.  aMax Reinhardt.  aPeter Zadek.  aRobert Sturua.  aRupert Goold.  aTrevor Nunn.  aanti-Semitism.  afilm.  aperformance.1 aBulman, J. C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSokolova, Boika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStavreva, Kirilka, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStavreva, Kirilka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526150103423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526150103/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPb2023